headline: Trade Desk, MP Materials, CoreWeave: Trending Tickers
summary: Trade Desk (TTD) stock is surging on news that the company will join the S&P 500 (^GSPC), replacing Ansys (ANSS). Robinhood (HOOD) and Applovin (APP) are trading slightly lower after not making the cut to join the index once again. Rare-earth miner MP Materials (MP) stock is soaring on reports of a $500 million investment from Apple (AAPL) tied to rare-earth magnets from its Texas plant, according to Fox Business and other sources. CoreWeave (CRWV) is planning to build a $6 billion artificial intelligence (AI) data center in Pennsylvania, which, according to Reuters, is part of a broader $70 billion push for US AI and energy infrastructure.
